<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-09-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-09-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="932" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d932">
                    <note rend="inline" type="source">540.61B3/262: Telegram</note>
                    <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            Chargé in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Keith</hi></persName>)</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-09-07T19:00:00-04:00">September 7, 1938—7
                            p.m.</date></dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>44. Your despatch no. 497, August 18, 1938.<note n="3" xml:id="d932fn3">Not
                            printed.</note> Please inform the Secretary General of the League of
                        Nations that the President has approved the designation of Mr. Curtis T.
                        Everett, American Consul at Geneva, as the delegate of the United States to
                        the conference in regard to the moving picture films convention. Everett is
                        also being informed to this effect.</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>